Business Brief -- Reebok International Ltd.:
   Firm Sees 4th-Quarter Net
   Close to Analysts' Estimates
Reebok shares fell $3.25 to close at $30 on New York Stock
Exchange composite volume of 2,832,000 shares.
   In a statement released after the close of trading, Reebok
said it will report record sales and earnings for the quarter
and that it is "pleased with the condition of its business."
Sales of Reebok brand footwear was up 12% over the 1990
fourth quarter, while sales of Reebok's International
division were up more than 54%, the company said. Backlog is
up 11% over last year's level, the Stoughton, Mass., company
said.